install nginx for config foe enabling port 80

go to /etc/nginx/sites-available and edit default file

https://github.com/npsoni88/tcsjenkins/blob/master/default

jenkins uname:sachin  passwd:sachin

groovy script for pipeline


Docker

docker ps - list the containers

docker ps -a - list the running containers

dokcer run - itd imageName - (-d detached mode ie comtainer runs in background)

docker stop cname - to stop

docker rm cname -to delete container

docker rm -i  - to delete an image

docker run -itd --name name imgName =to name the container

docker run -itd --name tcs_container -p 80:80(host:container)  nginx  -to map the container


docker exec -it tcs_container /bin/bash  -to get into the container from root

ctr p + ctrl q  - to get out of container(dont use exit)

Volume mounting

docker run -u root -d --name jenkins --rm -d -p 80:8080 -p 50000:50000 -v /root/workspace/jenkins_home:/var/jenkins_home  -v var/run/docker
.sock:/var/run/docker.sock  jenkinsci/jenkins
